generateCreationDateInCorrectFormat

public static String generateCreationDateInCorrectFormat(File image)
                                                  throws org.apache.sanselan.ImageReadException,
                                                         IOException,
                                                         ParseException
Helper to extract the date this image was created to be used during the renaming process.

In the EXIF standard itself the following convention for dates as is defined: D. Other Tags DateTime The date and time of image creation. In this standard it is the date and time the file was changed. The format is "YYYY:MM:DD HH:MM:SS" with time shown in 24-hour format, and the date and time separated by one blank character [20.H]. When the date and time are unknown, all the character spaces except colons (":") may be filled with blank characters, or else the Interoperability field may be filled with blank characters. The character string length is 20 bytes including NULL for termination. When the field is left blank, it is treated as unknown. Tag = 306 (132.H) Type = ASCII Count = 20 Default = none If the extracted date value is empty - no new file name is generated.

Parameters:
image - Image to extract metadata from.
Returns:
the date this image was created if found, format is
Throws:
ParseException - If metadata cannot be parsed correctly.
org.apache.sanselan.ImageReadException - If image cannot be read.
IOException - If an error occurs when accessing the image's metadata.
See Also:
Canon EXIF example page, EXIF specifications, EXIF2-2.pdf specification
